cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with generating 3D shapes from unstructured 2D image collections using deep neural networks and adversarial training. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for image processing and graphics (cs.GR) for rendering 3D shapes. The use of deep neural networks and adversarial training falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also involves optimization techniques for training the neural network, which falls under neural networks (cs.NE).
